INSERT INTO `ch_17` VALUES (1,'02 Which enzyme is responsible for\nthe conversion of inactivefibrinogens to fibrins?\n[NEET 2021]\n','(a) Thrombin','(b) Renin','(c) Epinephrine','(d) Thrombokinase\nAns.','(a)'),(2,'4 1 2 3','(a) 4 1 2 3','(b) 1 2 4 3','(c) 2 1 3 4','(d) 3 4 2 1\nAns.','(d)'),(3,'4 1 2 3','(a) Goblet cells','(b) Mucous cells','(c) Chief cells','(d) Parietal cellsAns.','(d)'),(4,'05 Match the items given in Column I\nwith those in Column II and selectthe\ncorrect option given below\n[NEET 2018]\nColumn I Column II\n1. Fibrinogen (i) Osmotic\nbalance\n2. Globulin (ii) Blood clotting3. Albumin (iii) Defence\nmechanism\n12 3\n','(a) (i) (iii) (ii)','(b) (i) (ii) (iii)','(c) (iii) (ii) (i)','(d) (ii) (iii) (i)\nAns.','(d)'),(5,'06 Adult human RBCs are enucleate.\nWhich of the following statement(s)is/are most appropriateexplanation for this feature?\n(I) They do not need to reproduce.\n[NEET 2017]\n(II) They are somatic cells.\n(III) They do not metabolise.\n(IV) All their internal space is\navailable for oxygen transport.\nCodes\n','(a) Only (IV)','(b) Only (I)','(c) (I), (III) and (IV)','(d) (II) and (III)\nAns.','(a)'),(6,'07 Name the blood cells, whose\nreduction in number can causeclotting disorder, leading toexcessive loss of blood from thebody.\n[NEET 2016, Phase II]\n','(a) Erythrocytes','(b) Leucocytes','(c) Neutrophils','(d) Thrombocytes\nAns.','(d)'),(7,'08 Serum differs from blood in\n[NEET 2016, Phase II]\n','(a) lacking globulins','(b) lacking albumins','(c) lacking clotting factors','(d) lacking antibodiesAns.','(c)'),(8,'09 Person with blood group AB is\nconsidered as universal recipientbecause he has\n[CBSE AIPMT 2014]\n','(a) Both A and B antigens on RBC but no\nantibodies in the plasma','(b) Both A and B antibodies in the plasma','(c) No antigen on RBC and no antibody in\nthe plasma','(d) Both A and B antigens in the plasma\nbut no antibodies\nAns.','(a)'),(9,'10 A certain road accident patient\nwith unknown blood group needsimmediate b